cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CV. 

This paper deals with sentence classification tasks, which are commonly studied in the natural language processing (NLP) field. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a method that uses multiple sentence vectors to fix the noise in the vectors, which involves machine learning techniques and could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of translations, which could be related to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CV (Computer Vision) if the translations are obtained from image captions or other visual data.
